lead_paragraph: With the season’s end drawing near, it is once again time for Ron Dayne, a backup running back for the Texans, to stand tall. In the team’s past two games, Dayne, filling in for the injured Ahman Green, has rumbled for 211 yards and a touchdown. Similarly, from Weeks 13 through 16 last season, Dayne amassed 429 yards and 5 touchdowns.
